<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id5b5dd4bd-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c" identifier="/us/usc/t29/s1906"><num value="1906">§ 1906.</num><heading> Construction; effect on agreements</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">This chapter shall not be construed as modifying or affecting any agreement between the Department of Education or any other department or agency of the United States and the Helen Keller Services for the Blind, Incorporated, or any successor to or assignee of such corporation, with respect to the Center.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id5b5dd4be-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/221/tII/s207">Pub. L. 98–221, title II, § 207</ref>, <date date="1984-02-22">Feb. 22, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/34">98 Stat. 34</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/102/569/tIX/s906">Pub. L. 102–569, title IX, § 906</ref>, <date date="1992-10-29">Oct. 29, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/4483">106 Stat. 4483</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
